    "Name": "Tolson",
    "Details": "Originally developed by the first Star League, the Tolson was designed to serve as the ultimate command and control and electronic warfare platform of its era. The Tolson TOL-5Nb is the so-called 'Royal' version of the design. Although the Tolson in general was quite high-tech by Star League standards, the -5Nb uses more advanced weaponry to up the ante in combat. Built on the same 300-rated XL engine with DHS and Ferro-Fibrous armor, the 'Royal' Tolson uses a LB-10X Autocannon and 4 Medium Pulse Lasers for firepower. It carries the same Command Console and Guardian ECM of its progenitor but drops the Narc, and TAG to instead carry a MASC system for extra speed.<br><br>S-class mechs feature upgrades to their armour, thermal management and defensive systems that substantially improve their survivability on the 31st century battlefield.",
